{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"71b37a1c-618b-4ecd-844c-a278e80dccc7","content":"With **MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0**, the change is straightforward. In your project file:\n\n**Remove** (or set to `false`):\n```xml\n<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n```\n\nThat's the key change — MSTest.Sdk **3.8.0 defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform** when `UseVSTest` is not set (or is `false`).\n\n### Other things to be aware of:\n\n1. **Running tests** — Use `dotnet test` as before; it works with both runners. You can also run the test executable directly (`./YourTests.exe`).\n\n2. **CLI differences** — Some VSTest CLI options (e.g., `--filter`) change syntax. The new platform uses `--filter` with the same expressions but some advanced VSTest-specific options may differ.\n\n3. **`.runsettings`** — Still supported, but review yours for any VSTest-specific adapter settings that may not carry over.\n\n4. **Extensions** — If you use VSTest-specific adapters/extensions (custom loggers, data collectors), check for Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalents.\n\n5. **CI pipelines** — If your CI uses `dotnet test --logger trx`, TRX logging still works but you may need the `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` package explicitly.\n\n### TL;DR\n\n```diff\n <Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n-    <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n </Project>\n```\n\nRemove the `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` line, rebuild, and run your tests to verify everything passes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1ebd6f6a-6512-48b7-9025-f04f8aeb82bb","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"No repo-specific content. I'll answer from my knowledge about the MSTest.Sdk migration from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform.","outputTokens":475,"requestId":"9C44:113D23:159DD72:18387C8:69F86179"},"id":"08a26fbe-6495-479e-ba6d-00fbe4f8e2ce","timestamp":"2026-05-04T09:06:13.584Z","parentId":"3fcc2e32-69e8-475f-804e-619a459abe5f"}
